---
/*
  DIY subpage 2 of 4 — How to Get Dumbphones (/diy/get-dumbphones).

  Sections, top to bottom (ticker, masthead, footer come from BaseLayout):
    1. Hero       — the M ❀ logo
    2. Heading    — cyan "* HOW TO GET DUMBPHONES" bar
    3. Body       — two blue sub-headings, a photo, and a black email CTA
    4. Next       — link forward to the next subpage in the read-in-order set

  No "Resources" section on this page (the design doesn't have one). The blue
  sub-headings reuse the home page's `.label` style; the black button mirrors
  the DIY landing page's Lydia call-to-action.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Hero from '../../components/Hero.astro';
import SectionHeader from '../../components/SectionHeader.astro';
import NextLink from '../../components/NextLink.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="How to Get Dumbphones — Month Offline" masthead="Month Offline > DIY Guide > Dumbphones">
  <div class="sections">
    <!-- 1. Hero -->
    <Hero />

    <!-- 2. Heading -->
    <SectionHeader label="How to get dumbphones" />

    <!-- 3. Body -->
    <section class="card">
      <h3 class="label">The dumbest phone company</h3>
      <p class="body">
        It's not every day that a tech startup grows out of an offline
        community, but <u>dumb.co</u> is just that! The dumbphone company was
        started by two of the MO founders and some of the very first
        participants. Inspired by the learnings and needs that came to light
        during the challenge, they built a dumbphone that makes it super easy
        for people to flip off.
      </p>

      <img
        class="card__photo"
        src="/images/dumbphones.png"
        width="1500"
        height="1000"
        alt="Participants gathered around a table setting up their dumbphones"
      />

      <h3 class="label">How it works</h3>
      <p class="body">
        dumb.co is offering free phones to all Month Offline participants. Upon
        receiving the phone, they will need to activate a $20.99/mo phone plan
        for a minimum of 2 months. Email lydia@offline.community to receive a
        promo code that you can share with your participants.
      </p>

      <!-- CTA out to dumb.co to order phones. -->
      <a class="order-btn font-display" href="https://dumb.co" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Order dumbphones</a>
    </section>

    <!-- 4. Next — read-in-order, per CLAUDE.md (Get Dumbphones → Facilitate Meetups → …). -->
    <NextLink label="How to Facilitate Meetups" href="/diy/facilitate-meetups" />
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* Standard body paragraph (Syne Mono). */
  .body {
    font-size: var(--size-body);
    line-height: var(--leading-body);
  }

  /* Blue sub-headings inside the card (same as the home page's "How it works"). */
  .label {
    font-size: var(--size-body);
    color: var(--mo-blue);
    letter-spacing: var(--track-label);
  }
  .label + .body {
    margin-top: var(--space-2);
  }

  /* The photo sits between the two sub-sections inside the white card. */
  .card__photo {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    margin: var(--space-3) 0;
  }

  /* Black CTA button (white text), mirroring the landing page's Lydia button. */
  .order-btn {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    margin-top: var(--space-3);
    padding: var(--space-2);
    background: var(--black);
    color: var(--white);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-size: var(--size-body);
  }
</style>
